{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> παραπίπτω</b>, <br /> <b>fall beside</b>, ἐγγὺς τῶν τειχῶν -πεπτωκός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lysander” 29 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>come side to side</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 718a1, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Mathematics texts, as <i>passive</i> of παραβάλλω, <b>to be applied</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Archimedes Geometra “περὶ κωνοειδέων καὶ σφαιροειδέων” 2. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>fall in one's way</b>, κατὰ τύχην παραπεσοῦσα νηῦς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.87, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 27.15; ἀκοντίσαι ὅπου ἂν παραπίπτῃ [θηρίον] 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.10; ἀγοράσαι.. χιτωνάριον, μάλιστα μὲν ἐὰν παραπίπτῃ χειριδωτόν “PCair.Zen.” 469.5 (3rd c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. κατὰ βοήθειαν <b>come in time</b> to aid, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 31.5.2, etc.\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; ὁπότε καιρὸς παραπέσοι as opportunity <b>offered</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitum magistro” 7.4, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.23; οὐ δεῖ τοιοῦτον παραπεπτωκότα καιρὸν ἀφεῖναι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 1.8; εἴ ποθεν ἄελπτος παραπέσοι σωτηρία 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1173; ὁ -πίπτων παρὰ τῶν πολλῶν ἔπαινος 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Gnomologium Vaticanum - Kleine Schriften” 29 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ παραπεσών <b>the first that comes</b>, ἡ παραπίπτουσα ἀεὶ [ἡδονή] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 561b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ παραπεπτωκὼς λόγος <b>that happened to arise</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 832b, compare “Phlb.” 14c \">Refs</a>]; πᾶν τὸ παραπῖπτον or παραπεσόν all <b>that befalls</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.51.5, 11.4.5 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; κατὰ τὸ -πῖπτον <b>incidentally</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Morte - Papiri Ercolanesi” 37. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>dative</i>, <b>befall</b>, θαυμαστὸν κτῆμα παραπεσεῖν τοῖς Ἕλλησι <b>fell to</b> their <b>lot</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 686d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. τῇ πόλει νομοθέτης <b>comes to</b> its <b>aid</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 709c: in bad sense, ἀσθένειά τινι παραπεπτωκυῖα 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ παρρησίας” p.49O.; παραπέπτωκε τῇ πόλει ὥστε ἀνακτᾶσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Vectigalibus” 5.8. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>fall, rush in</b>, εἰς τὸ Σαμικόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.80.9, etc. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>go astray, err</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.6.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖς ὅλοις πράγμασιν ἀγνοεῖν καὶ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 18.36.6; π. τῇ διανοίᾳ Vett. Val. 73.25. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__IV.b</b></Level4> <b>to be mislaid</b> or <b>lost</b>, of a document, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Ostr.Bodl.” i62 (2nd c.BC), “POxy.” 95.34 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>], etc.; σανδάλιον παραπεσόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 27. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.2</b></Level3> <b>fall aside</b> or <b>away from</b>, with <i>genitive</i>, τῆς ὁδοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.54.5; τῆς ἀληθείας [prev. author] 12.12.2; τοῦ καθήκοντος [prev. author] 8.11.8; τῆς ἱστορίας 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.1.7 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>fall away,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"NT.Heb.6.6. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>fall down before, cringe, flatter</b>, παραπεπτωκώς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 45.84. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VI</b></Level2> Astrology texts, <b>to be unfavourably situated</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 5.5, 27.18. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3895","accentedUnicode":"παραπίπτω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3844","matchingForm":"παρά","stepTransliteration":"para","gloss":"from/with/beside","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從, 在, 邊…","_es_Gloss":"de/con/al lado","_zh_Gloss":"从, 在, 边…"},{"strongNumber":"G3900","matchingForm":"παράπτωμα","stepTransliteration":"paraptōma","gloss":"trespass","_zh_tw_Gloss":"過犯","_es_Gloss":"transgresión","_zh_Gloss":"过犯"},{"strongNumber":"G4098","matchingForm":"πίπτω","stepTransliteration":"piptō","gloss":"to collapse","_zh_tw_Gloss":"落","_es_Gloss":"colapsar","_zh_Gloss":"落"}],"shortDef":"to fall away, commit apostasy defect","mediumDef":"to fall away, commit apostasy defect <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>to fall by the side of;</b> <i>metaphorically</i> <b>to fall off</b> or <b>away from, make defection from, commit apostasy</b> <ref='Heb.6.6'>Heb. 6:6</ref>*","stepGloss":"to defect","stepTransliteration":"parapiptō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"apostatar, cometer apostasía","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 掉在旁邊, 走錯路<br>2) 偏離, 離經叛道 (來 6:6)","_zh_Definition":"1) 掉在旁边, 走错路<br>2) 偏离, 离经叛道 (来 6:6)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"sa ngã","_zh_tw_Gloss":"背離了","_es_Gloss":"desertar","_zh_Gloss":"背离了"}]}